1️⃣ Create Django Project

In your terminal:

django-admin startproject messaging_app

2️⃣ Install Django REST Framework

Inside your virtual environment, run:

pip install djangorestframework


You may also create a requirements.txt:

pip freeze > requirements.txt

3️⃣ Configure REST Framework in settings.py

Open:

messaging_app/messaging_app/settings.py


Add rest_framework to INSTALLED_APPS:

INSTALLED_APPS = [
    'django.contrib.admin',
    'django.contrib.auth',
    'django.contrib.contenttypes',
    'django.contrib.sessions',
    'django.contrib.messages',
    'django.contrib.staticfiles',
    'rest_framework',
    'chats',
]

(Optional but recommended) Add REST framework config:

REST_FRAMEWORK = {
    'DEFAULT_PERMISSION_CLASSES': [
        'rest_framework.permissions.AllowAny',
    ]
}

4️⃣ Create Chats App
cd messaging_app
python manage.py startapp chats

